Imagine all of you

00:49:56.000 --> 00:50:00.823
looking like military bowls sitting down here. How will it look?

00:50:01.024 --> 00:50:03.311
You have to be people of variety,

00:50:03.512 --> 00:50:06.079
so God has created a beautiful variety.

00:50:06.280 --> 00:50:07.559
Enjoy that!

00:50:07.760 --> 00:50:09.959
Enjoy the integration of that variety.

00:50:10.160 --> 00:50:12.680
That is what one has to really enjoy,

00:50:12.881 --> 00:50:15.800
but I think it's only possible when you get your Realization.

00:50:16.000 --> 00:50:19.529
Before that it's just talk, talk and talk.

00:50:20.513 --> 00:50:22.479
So now we come to the third center -

00:50:22.680 --> 00:50:26.152
I won't be able to cover all of them today, I'm sorry -

00:50:27.195 --> 00:50:31.895
which is very important because it is the center of your seeking.

00:50:32.628 --> 00:50:35.439
First, we seek as animals our food.

00:50:35.640 --> 00:50:38.093
Even now, we behave like animals, no doubt.

00:50:38.294 --> 00:50:40.800
So, we seek food, the attention is only on food.

00:50:41.009 --> 00:50:43.039
Anybody talks of food,

00:50:43.240 --> 00:50:45.479
we want to turn our face to that.

00:50:45.680 --> 00:50:49.199
So, the food is the first seeking we had.

00:50:49.400 --> 00:50:52.760
The second seeking we had of shelter,

00:50:53.000 --> 00:50:55.519
to have a proper shelter,

00:50:55.720 --> 00:50:58.900
and that has gone beyond any human understanding.

00:50:59.101 --> 00:51:02.164
I have seen people building houses

00:51:02.418 --> 00:51:05.491
which look like nothing on earth, you know.

00:51:05.692 --> 00:51:07.341
We just can't say this is a house,

00:51:07.550 --> 00:51:11.326
I mean, it's some sort of a funny thing that they make -

00:51:11.533 --> 00:51:14.360
call it a house - where you feel you are in a nightmare, you see,

00:51:14.600 --> 00:51:17.880
the way it is built upside down, going like that and...

00:51:18.040 --> 00:51:20.996
You don't know what sort of a place it is and where you are living.

00:51:21.197 --> 00:51:24.120
And that has gone to such a limit, specially in America I find

00:51:24.320 --> 00:51:25.931
that you have to enter into any bathroom

00:51:26.132 --> 00:51:28.532
first enquire how to open,

00:51:29.725 --> 00:51:32.357
otherwise you'll have a problem. Such varieties.

00:51:32.558 --> 00:51:34.960
Like into one bathroom who was a very reach man's

00:51:35.120 --> 00:51:38.372
I placed My foot and I was drenched in water. I said, "What's that?

00:51:38.573 --> 00:51:40.028
From where is it coming?"

00:51:40.229 --> 00:51:45.080
So, this kind of an unnecessary mental exercise

00:51:45.280 --> 00:51:47.680
to select even the handle of the car.

00:51:47.881 --> 00:51:50.269
If the handle of the car you don't know, better don't get in

00:51:50.470 --> 00:51:52.340
because something happens you can't get out

00:51:52.541 --> 00:51:54.959
because you don't know how to open the car.

00:51:55.160 --> 00:51:58.398
It's such a madness to go on worrying

00:51:58.599 --> 00:52:01.440
about the varieties of little, little, little, little things.

00:52:01.641 --> 00:52:04.853
You know what kind of a thing - like today I went for shopping

00:52:05.054 --> 00:52:07.759
and there were some ladies who were trying to decide

00:52:07.960 --> 00:52:10.760
what kind of a ladle they should have.

00:52:10.960 --> 00:52:13.599
Hours they took to decide for a ladle.

00:52:13.800 --> 00:52:16.040
Can you imagine? What difference does it make

00:52:16.241 --> 00:52:18.400
of one ladle or the other ladle?

00:52:18.600 --> 00:52:23.320
And tomorrow if they see somebody else having a more modern stuff,

00:52:23.521 --> 00:52:25.325
they'll again be back and to find out

00:52:25.524 --> 00:52:27.639
that more modern stuff to do it.

00:52:27.840 --> 00:52:32.494
I mean to amount of decision taking we have gone is maddening.

00:52:33.400 --> 00:52:35.960
Specially on a table, if you go,

00:52:36.120 --> 00:52:38.920
I have seen people - because I have to attend so many parties -

00:52:39.120 --> 00:52:40.320
I just can't understand,

00:52:40.560 --> 00:52:44.050
half an hour they discuss what they are going to have today.

00:52:44.504 --> 00:52:46.479
I mean everybody must have what they want

00:52:46.680 --> 00:52:48.266
and very particular on that point.

00:52:48.467 --> 00:52:51.479
When the food comes they see they have got the same thing or not.

00:52:51.680 --> 00:52:54.534
What is so important? The whole joy of eating,

00:52:54.735 --> 00:52:56.301
the whole joy of meeting,

00:52:56.525 --> 00:52:59.399
everything is lost in that nonsense of decision.

00:52:59.600 --> 00:53:01.993
What does it matter whether you eat a pizza

00:53:02.194 --> 00:53:04.120
or you eat that, I don't understand.

00:53:04.321 --> 00:53:07.418
At the most you can have one thing for all of you and just enjoy it.

00:53:07.619 --> 00:53:12.240
But on the contrary, so much time we waste on nonsensical things,

00:53:12.475 --> 00:53:17.400
and when we do that we develop funny diseases within ourselves,

00:53:18.160 --> 00:53:20.920
because we put our nerves to too much tension.

00:53:21.120 --> 00:53:23.640
It is too much of a tension for us.

00:53:23.840 --> 00:53:26.879
We build up our own tensions for everything.

00:53:27.080 --> 00:53:28.960
I have ordered for this, you have got this.

00:53:29.160 --> 00:53:31.839
I wanted this kind of a handle, I got this one.

00:53:31.959 --> 00:53:35.599
That's how we go on building up tensions in our stomachs,

00:53:35.800 --> 00:53:38.600
and then we talk of our tensions. We have tensions,

00:53:38.807 --> 00:53:42.482
and we have this tension and that tension, and what is to be done?

00:53:43.120 --> 00:53:48.137
And then we get people coming out in the market.

00:53:49.120 --> 00:53:53.168
They want six thousand pounds to reduce your stomach tension.

00:53:53.960 --> 00:53:56.959
How can they reduce? They cannot.

00:53:57.160 --> 00:54:00.280
And you believe it, because they advertise very well.

00:54:00.520 --> 00:54:03.181
They put up a big show, "We'll remove your tensions

00:54:03.382 --> 00:54:05.840
and we are here for your tensions, and this and that."

00:54:06.041 --> 00:54:08.760
And you just go there and attend to them,

00:54:08.960 --> 00:54:12.079
and you think, "Oh, now we have removed our tension".

00:54:12.280 --> 00:54:15.534
Mentally you feel like that but the tension is all there.

00:54:16.371 --> 00:54:21.342
That's how we build up our stomach in a very funny way.

00:54:21.626 --> 00:54:25.737
Our real seeking should not be in politics,

00:54:26.600 --> 00:54:30.291
should not be in any social behaviour,

00:54:30.492 --> 00:54:34.649
but it should be only towards our ascent,

00:54:35.730 --> 00:54:37.439
towards our Spirit.

00:54:37.640 --> 00:54:39.680
That should be our seeking,

00:54:39.881 --> 00:54:41.960
and when that stage comes in

00:54:42.161 --> 00:54:45.304
then they are the people of a special category

00:54:45.505 --> 00:54:47.522
which William Blake has described

00:54:47.723 --> 00:54:49.808
that the men of God,

00:54:50.009 --> 00:54:53.680
means the people of this special category, will become prophets,

00:54:53.881 --> 00:54:56.280
and they will have power to make others prophets.

00:54:56.481 --> 00:54:58.800
And that's the time, today we are here

00:54:59.001 --> 00:55:03.890
that those who are men of God will become prophets

00:55:04.091 --> 00:55:07.119
and they will have powers to make others prophets.

00:55:07.320 --> 00:55:11.236
That is the sign, that if you can make others prophet as you are

00:55:11.437 --> 00:55:13.210
then you have achieved your goal

00:55:13.411 --> 00:55:15.639
and that should be the real seeking.

00:55:15.840 --> 00:55:19.319
Politics is a mad world, you know that.

00:55:19.520 --> 00:55:22.399
It's a mad world. And is a mythical thing

00:55:22.600 --> 00:55:25.239
because when we talk

00:55:25.440 --> 00:55:27.759
of capitalism,

00:55:27.960 --> 00:55:30.215
what is your capital?

00:55:30.960 --> 00:55:35.239
These worldly things, these stones, these plastics?

00:55:35.440 --> 00:55:38.298
What are your possessions?

00:55:39.280 --> 00:55:43.710
You have one possession which you do not know - that is your Spirit.

00:55:43.911 --> 00:55:47.737
The one who has known that possession is a real capitalist.

00:55:48.594 --> 00:55:53.317
And once he becomes that capitalist he spreads it, automatically.

00:55:53.518 --> 00:55:57.120
For example, Me, I am a very happily married woman,

00:55:57.320 --> 00:55:59.137
extremely happily married woman

00:55:59.338 --> 00:56:03.039
with a very good husband, very well-placed in life

00:56:03.240 --> 00:56:05.999
with very good children, grandchildren,

00:56:06.200 --> 00:56:08.400
very good family life, everything there,

00:56:08.520 --> 00:56:10.759
but I can't enjoy it,

00:56:10.960 --> 00:56:13.199
because I have to give this.

00:56:13.400 --> 00:56:17.239
So, I become a communist in that way, in the real sense of the word.

00:56:17.440 --> 00:56:20.079
I am a real capitalist and a real communist.

00:56:20.280 --> 00:56:22.759
I spend My own money,

00:56:22.960 --> 00:56:26.239
go and meet people, talk to them, make them understand

00:56:26.440 --> 00:56:29.280
and ask them to be their Spirits,

00:56:29.440 --> 00:56:33.025
to be themselves, to be their own power.

00:56:33.226 --> 00:56:35.040
For what? People don't understand.

00:56:35.241 --> 00:56:37.479
The people who are with My husband,

00:56:37.680 --> 00:56:39.520
their wives say, "What are you doing?"

00:56:39.760 --> 00:56:42.639
"Oh, why are you wasting your time?"

00:56:42.840 --> 00:56:45.760
They can't understand, "What is She up to?"

00:56:45.961 --> 00:56:48.322
because they are busy with other things,

00:56:48.523 --> 00:56:50.630
joyless pursuits.

00:56:51.178 --> 00:56:53.805
But I am here, working for you,

00:56:54.006 --> 00:56:56.039
working for everyone,

00:56:56.240 --> 00:57:00.395
just that you also enjoy what I am enjoying.

00:57:00.596 --> 00:57:02.056
So politics is all nonsense,

00:57:02.257 --> 00:57:04.612
it has no meaning at all, you can see that clearly.

00:57:04.813 --> 00:57:07.960
That's why no politics has been successful.

00:57:08.161 --> 00:57:11.920
I've been to Russia, it's another gone case; I've been to America.

00:57:12.121 --> 00:57:15.559
We do not know how to bear our freedom.

00:57:15.760 --> 00:57:17.338
We don't know.

00:57:17.539 --> 00:57:19.919
We don't know, we want to have freedom of

00:57:20.120 --> 00:57:24.969
Abraham Lincoln said that, because he was a realized soul,

00:57:25.170 --> 00:57:27.559
but he didn't know that all the others are not.

00:57:27.760 --> 00:57:32.159
Once you have your freedom, you go to abandonment, violence,

00:57:32.360 --> 00:57:34.362
you don't know how to be free.

00:57:34.563 --> 00:57:36.080
That glory is not within us,

00:57:36.281 --> 00:57:40.199
to be free you have to be a king, to be a free personality.

00:57:40.400 --> 00:57:44.079
If you are not that than you go hither, thither, do this, do that.

00:57:44.280 --> 00:57:47.342
All the time what you do is self-destruction.

00:57:47.543 --> 00:57:51.039
Morning till evening you are thinking how to destroy yourself.

00:57:51.240 --> 00:57:55.330
Ultimately, all those who are affluent

00:57:55.531 --> 00:57:57.759
democratic countries

00:57:57.960 --> 00:58:00.719
if you meet their young people, if you ask them

00:58:00.920 --> 00:58:02.519
you'll be amazed

00:58:02.720 --> 00:58:06.199
that they are doing nothing but planning about their suicide,

00:58:06.400 --> 00:58:09.759
which is the most sophisticated way of committing suicide.

00:58:09.960 --> 00:58:12.839
Can you believe it? That's a fact.

00:58:13.040 --> 00:58:15.600
We had three girls from Sweden, very young girls -

00:58:15.801 --> 00:58:18.319
in Cambridge they came to see Me -

00:58:18.520 --> 00:58:20.840
and when they came to see Me and I felt their vibrations

00:58:21.041 --> 00:58:22.934
I was shocked, I said, "Oh God,

00:58:23.135 --> 00:58:25.360
they have vibrations just like a dead man is.

00:58:25.520 --> 00:58:29.182
Is numb, complete numb." I said, "What are you doing?"

00:58:29.838 --> 00:58:33.040
They said, "You know, we think we are worth nothing. It's useless".

00:58:33.240 --> 00:58:36.199
I said, "Why? You are rich people, you have so much money,

00:58:36.400 --> 00:58:39.559
you are very well off, you have a very organized country,

00:58:39.760 --> 00:58:41.650
and everything is fine.

00:58:41.851 --> 00:58:43.711
What, what's the matter with you?"

00:58:43.912 --> 00:58:48.592
They said: "Actually, we are all planning how to commit suicide".

00:58:49.697 --> 00:58:52.359
This is where you go with your affluence,

00:58:52.560 --> 00:58:55.079
with your so-called achievements,

00:58:55.280 --> 00:58:57.693
that either you try to destroy yourself,

00:58:57.894 --> 00:58:59.310
or try to commit suicide,

00:58:59.511 --> 00:59:02.640
or can have a collective destruction

00:59:02.840 --> 00:59:07.225
by your great achievements of science.

00:59:08.201 --> 00:59:11.617
Because we do not know what freedom is.

00:59:11.818 --> 00:59:15.059
We do not know how much God has worked out

00:59:15.260 --> 00:59:17.519
to create these beautiful human beings,

00:59:17.720 --> 00:59:21.141
how beautiful, fantastic we are within ourselves.

00:59:21.342 --> 00:59:23.800
Because we have no idea as to what we are,

00:59:24.001 --> 00:59:26.518
that's why we accept all these things,

00:59:26.719 --> 00:59:29.575
go on living with it and destroy ourselves.

00:59:29.909 --> 00:59:34.650
So the main seeking within us is the seeking for God,

00:59:34.851 --> 00:59:37.119
seeking for our evolution,

00:59:37.320 --> 00:59:43.359
seeking for our higher dimension of collective consciousness.

00:59:43.560 --> 00:59:45.523
And that is what we have to achieve.

00:59:45.724 --> 00:59:50.622
Without that this world cannot be saved, cannot be emancipated.

00:59:50.823 --> 00:59:55.316
There's no other way out but the transformation of human beings.

00:59:55.517 --> 00:59:59.079
It's only the transformation that is going to work it out,

00:59:59.280 --> 01:00:01.079
nothing else.

01:00:01.280 --> 01:00:04.409
The time is short, one has to get transformed.

01:00:04.610 --> 01:00:08.039
Only those who will be transformed will be saved,

01:00:08.240 --> 01:00:12.199
all the rest will be sorted out at the end of the era,

01:00:12.400 --> 01:00:14.828
when you will find

01:00:16.200 --> 01:00:18.472
someone

01:00:19.680 --> 01:00:23.879
extremely powerful, destructive will come on this earth

01:00:24.080 --> 01:00:28.053
and will destroy everything else.

01:00:28.254 --> 01:00:33.767
Because that is what according to that personality

01:00:33.968 --> 01:00:36.419
would be the end,

01:00:36.620 --> 01:00:41.110
that would be a deserving punishment.

01:00:42.082 --> 01:00:44.239
So one has to get transformation.

01:00:44.440 --> 01:00:47.931
That is the time that is given to us -

01:00:48.729 --> 01:00:51.596
is called as Krita Yuga in Sanskrit language -

01:00:51.797 --> 01:00:54.739
means this is the time when the All-Pervading Power,

01:00:54.940 --> 01:00:57.284
the Brahma Shakti, is working it out.

01:00:57.485 --> 01:00:58.919
Better get it out.

01:00:59.120 --> 01:01:00.719
This is the Blossom time,

01:01:00.920 --> 01:01:03.839
better get it transformation within yourself,

01:01:04.040 --> 01:01:08.563
establish yourself as transformed human beings.

01:01:08.764 --> 01:01:10.759
Don't get to your egos.

01:01:10.960 --> 01:01:14.799
Don't mislead others, don't mislead yourself.

01:01:15.000 --> 01:01:19.759
I tell you, intelligence itself is such a funny thing;

01:01:19.960 --> 01:01:23.079
it has a capacity to cheat itself.

01:01:23.280 --> 01:01:25.846
This is the worst thing of intelligence is

01:01:26.045 --> 01:01:28.216
that it can cheat itself.

01:01:28.417 --> 01:01:31.575
So, this living process has to work out within us

01:01:31.776 --> 01:01:37.035
so that we achieve our seeking, our fulfillment, our absolute.

01:01:37.499 --> 01:01:41.276
And that is something that cannot be discussed,

01:01:41.477 --> 01:01:43.182
talked about. It has to happen.

01:01:43.383 --> 01:01:46.479
Supposing, you want to know it on your mental level,

01:01:46.680 --> 01:01:48.960
I can only take you up to a point

01:01:49.161 --> 01:01:55.389
and find for you some sort of a logical conclusion.

01:01:55.590 --> 01:01:58.546
But ascending is your own.

01:01:58.747 --> 01:02:00.514
I cannot guarantee that.

01:02:00.768 --> 01:02:02.519
If it works out, well and good;

01:02:02.720 --> 01:02:06.239
if it does not, I cannot say that I can do it,

01:02:06.479 --> 01:02:08.189
nor can I say you can do it.

01:02:08.390 --> 01:02:10.280
But once it happens, of course,

01:02:10.520 --> 01:02:14.199
you can give it to others, and to others, and to others.

01:02:14.347 --> 01:02:17.167
You can work it out also, the same way,

01:02:17.368 --> 01:02:21.280
as one light which is enlightened can enlighten another light,

01:02:21.481 --> 01:02:23.876
and you can go on enlightening others.

01:02:24.077 --> 01:02:28.365
A gentleman in India, who was not a very educated man, a farmer,

01:02:28.566 --> 01:02:32.427
has given Realization to more than ten thousand people.

01:02:32.628 --> 01:02:36.478
So you can imagine how one can be powerful.

01:02:36.679 --> 01:02:40.487
I wish he had come to America but he had to go back to India.

01:02:40.688 --> 01:02:42.599
He came all the way to England

01:02:42.800 --> 01:02:46.889
then he went round with Me to Europe where

01:02:48.080 --> 01:02:51.153
he explained to people things in such a way,

01:02:51.354 --> 01:02:54.919
that they were surprised, an uneducated man

01:02:55.120 --> 01:02:57.000
talking like such a great saint.

01:02:57.240 --> 01:03:00.278
They could not understand how can he talk like that.

01:03:00.479 --> 01:03:02.119
I asked him, "How are you?"

01:03:02.320 --> 01:03:04.159
"Are you all right, are you comfortable?"

01:03:04.360 --> 01:03:07.505
He says one Marathi words he says,

01:03:07.706 --> 01:03:10.119
[Marathi].

01:03:10.320 --> 01:03:13.244
"Whatever is the Eternal, wherever it keeps you

01:03:13.445 --> 01:03:15.051
let the Eternal look after me."

01:03:15.252 --> 01:03:17.624
Means when you are worried about the eternal,

01:03:17.825 --> 01:03:19.243
when you are in the eternal,

01:03:19.444 --> 01:03:21.676
why are you worried about these transitory things?

01:03:21.877 --> 01:03:24.372
And I was so happy to hear these words from him.

01:03:24.573 --> 01:03:27.662
But there's one thing I must say that

01:03:27.863 --> 01:03:31.040
he was a fortunate man

01:03:31.240 --> 01:03:36.310
to be born in a country where they know about it;

01:03:37.690 --> 01:03:40.246
and more fortunate to be born in Maharashtra

01:03:40.447 --> 01:03:42.032
which is a country of saints

01:03:42.233 --> 01:03:45.140
who have written beautiful things

01:03:46.400 --> 01:03:48.917
and that country which is not so materialistic.

01:03:49.118 --> 01:03:52.950
For them materialistic achievements is not the success.

01:03:53.151 --> 01:03:55.459
That's why people don't understand. They always ask,

01:03:55.684 --> 01:03:57.719
"Then why people in India are poor?"

01:03:57.920 --> 01:03:59.599
I said, "Not at hearts".

01:03:59.800 --> 01:04:02.611
They are smiling, laughing, festive people.

01:04:02.812 --> 01:04:05.486
If you go to even a poor man's house,

01:04:05.687 --> 01:04:10.193
they will offer you a cup of milk. They have a large heart.

01:04:10.394 --> 01:04:11.709
Why they are poor?

01:04:11.910 --> 01:04:16.145
The reasons are we were slaves for three hundred years.

01:04:17.000 --> 01:04:20.122
Can you think of slavery of three hundred years?

01:04:20.328 --> 01:04:22.651
Who is responsible for that?

01:04:23.320 --> 01:04:24.839
Who made us poor?

01:04:25.040 --> 01:04:28.253
We would have been much richer than anyone of these countries.

01:04:28.454 --> 01:04:30.146
We were, once upon a time,

01:04:30.347 --> 01:04:33.012
the richest people in the whole world.

01:04:33.704 --> 01:04:38.119
There is a rich site called the richest site of the world in Iran,

01:04:38.320 --> 01:04:40.360
is a hall four times bigger than this,

01:04:40.561 --> 01:04:45.559
and the every, the door that opens into it is six feet wide.

01:04:45.760 --> 01:04:48.079
And when you go inside, what do you find?

01:04:48.280 --> 01:04:51.840
A gentleman called Muhammad Ghazni who invaded India,

01:04:52.040 --> 01:04:54.719
only about six hundred years back

01:04:54.920 --> 01:04:59.393
and carried all the gold and wealth of one temple.

